headline.main: ALFRED E. SMITH DIES HERE AT 70; 4 TIMES GOVERNOR; End Comes After a Sudden Relapse Following Earlier Turn for the Better RAN FOR PRESIDENT IN '28 His Rise From Newsboy and Fishmonger Had No Exact Parallel in U.S. History ALFRED E. SMITH DIES HERE AT 70

snippet: Alfred Emanuel Smith, four times Governor of this State, who rose from the sidewalks of New York to eminence in public life and in the hearts of many Americans, died early today at the age of 70 in Rockefeller Institute Hospital.
